  "commentary": "With SPX at 6605.48 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6607 in a PIN regime, dealers are positioned as stabilizers who will sell any push toward the massive +64B gamma wall at 6610 and buy dips toward the -27B negative gamma pocket at 6590. The recent wall break and 25% GEX surge suggests we just saw significant options flow that has dealers scrambling to hedge, likely creating the current mean-reverting setup. Key levels: 6590 downside magnet where dealers become buyers, 6607 flip point, and the 6610-6620 resistance zone where dealer selling pressure intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect prices to get pulled back toward 6600-6605 with limited upside past 6610.",
